<paragraph blockId="45.[313,1269,1128,1375]" pageId="45" pageNumber="2257">
Described as a new species by Norman (1935a: 23) on the basis of Irvine material. Maximum size of specimens is 
<quantity box="[677,762,1286,1311]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" pageId="45" pageNumber="2257" unit="cm" value="18.5">18.5 cm</quantity>
but Irvine indicated that it is said to grow to a length of 
<quantity box="[484,594,1319,1343]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="45" pageNumber="2257" unit="cm" value="75.0" valueMax="90.0" valueMin="60.0">60–90 cm</quantity>
. Irvine noted that another specimen (not found) taken at Accra in 1935 (Irvine 308) might belong to this genus.
</paragraph>
